1)     HOW TO USE
===================
1.1)   REQUIREMENTS
===================
       A C++ compiler (e.g. g++) and the GNU GSL library as well as an implementation of LAPACKE are required.
       (in Debian or Ubuntu systems the command "sudo apt-get install liblapacke liblapacke-dev libgsl-dev libgsl23 libgslcblas0" should suffice)

1.2)   DOCUMENTATION
====================
	   See doxygen output in ./doxygen/html/index.html or in ./doxygen/latex/*.pdf
	   for class documentation (build using command: doxygen ConcentricInterpolation.doxy)

1.3)   COMPILATION and EXAMPLE
==============================
1.3a)  For the LIBRARY, go to the "src" directory and run "make lib" on a terminal (adjust Makefile if required)
1.3b)  For an EXAMPLE, change to the "examples" directory. Call
	   make demo
       therein. Execution of the demo: change to the "bin" directory and execute
	   ./interpolation_demo ../data/directions/demo/dir_D3_N256_s0_e0.txt ../data/directions/demo/dir_D3_N10000_EQ.txt ../data/demo_output.txt
	   Plot results: change to the data directory and execute (requires additional software)
       gnuplot plot_3d_data.gp
       Follow the instructions on the terminal. This shows the result interpolating the function [0 0 1] * x at radius 5.


